  "lastUpdatedOn": "2012-04-13",
  "religion": "Abdul was raised a Jew and still keeps the faith to this day.",
  "politicalViews": "Abdul was very excited about Barack Obama's 2008 presidential victory, so the assumption is that she's a Democrat. There's not much more to go on.",
  "author": "Tom Kershaw",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Paula Abdul was born in San Fernando, California."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Both of her parents are Jewish. Her father is a middle-eastern Jew who emigrated to Brazil and then the United States and her mother, a Canadian woman whose Jewish ancestry is from Eastern Europe. Abdul explained it herself, saying:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 4,
      "parentId": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "My father is a Syrian Jew whose family immigrated to Brazil. My mother is Canadian with Jewish roots. My dream is to come to Israel for a real holiday.",
      "sourceTitle": "Israel Minister, American Ido",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-3328923,00.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "She got her wish and was invited to a vacation in Israel by Israeli Tourist Minister Isaac Herzog over the Hanukah Holiday Season in 2006.",
      "sourceTitle": "Israel Minister, American Ido",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-3328923,00.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Abdul was described by her own rabbi, Chaim Mentz, as a \"good Jewish girl\" and it is reported that she practices by regularly attending services and lighting Sabbath candles.",
      "sourceTitle": "Paula Abdul… \"a good Jewish girl.\"",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1yYrLwO0cIk"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " She has also spoken about bonding with some of the Jewish "
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "emphasis",
      "text": "American Idol"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " contestants over religion.",
      "sourceTitle": "Paula Abdul",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.nndb.com/people/883/000025808/"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "parentId": 7,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Politics cuts into my drinking time!"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Abdul is not well-known for her discourse on politics or society. She claims that she's not stupid, though, saying:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 10,
      "parentId": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 10,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I'm intelligent…I have a brain.",
      "sourceTitle": "Paula Abdul: 'I Have a Brain And Have Never Been Drunk in My Life.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.buzzfeed.com/mjs538/paula-abdul-i-am-intelligent"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "parentId": 11,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "She doesn't show it much."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 12
    },
    {
      "parentId": 12,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Abdul is heavily involved in various charities–signaling a desire to create a better world and society–but most of them, if not all, involve non-political topics.",
      "sourceTitle": "Paula Abdul",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/737-paula-abdul"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 13
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "She did signal extreme satisfaction when Barack Obama was elected as president in 2008, saying:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 15,
      "parentId": 14
    },
    {
      "parentId": 15,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I was crying [when I heard Obama had won]! You feel such a sense of pride that you can't even articulate how good you feel. It's unbelievable! I have chills. I was just so excited. I was texting everyone: 'Peace has begun.' And then I was texting everyone, 'I don't have to move to Vancouver now!'",
      "sourceTitle": "Paula Abdul: Obama Victory Triggers Tears and Texting",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20238768,00.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 16
    },
    {
      "parentId": 16,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I guess we can call her a Democrat, but, unfortunately, that's the only evidence."
    }
  ],
